statement.p:
Fill in the blanks with the numbers 44 and 99 (using each number only once) to create an equation where x has the greatest possible value.




 {}+x={} 




 {}={} {}\cdot x

webwork-reps.pg:
############################################# ### Generated from PreTeXt source ### ### https://pretextbook.org ### ############################################# ## DBsubject() ## DBchapter() ## DBsection() ## Level() ## KEYWORDS() ## TitleText1() ## EditionText1() ## AuthorText1() ## Section1(not reported) ## Problem1(A.7.6.50) ## Author() ## Institution() ## Language(en-US)
DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context('Numeric'); $little = random(10,50,2); $big = random(53,99,2);
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Fill in the blanks with the numbers [$little] and [$big] (using each number only once) to create an equation where [`x`] has the greatest possible value. a. [_]{$little}{3} [`{}+x={}`] [_]{$big}{3}
a. [_]{$big}{3} [`{}={}`] [_]{$little}{3}[`{}\cdot x`]
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. Consider which is greater: [`[$big] - [$little]`] or [`[$little] - [$big]\text{?}`] To make the largest value for [`x\text{,}`] you must put [$little] in the left blank and [$big] in the right blank because you solve this equation by subtracting [$little] from both sides. This makes [`x = [$big] - [$little]\text{,}`] which is the largest possible value for [`x\text{.}`]
a. Consider which is larger: [`\frac{[$big]}{[$little]}`] or [`\frac{[$little]}{[$big]}\text{?}`] To make the largest value for [`x\text{,}`] you must put [$big] in the left blank and [$little] in the right blank because you solve this equation by dividing both sides by [$little]. This makes [`x = \frac{[$big]}{[$little]}\text{,}`] which is the largest possible value for [`x\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();
